OL,3,CMan's arms 'completely exploded' after
OL,4,Ctouching 11,000 volts of electricity
OL,6,FHe had burns to his face, arms, chest
OL,7,Fand abdomen. He lost his left thumb,
OL,8,Fboth ears and the tip of his nose.
OL,10,FHe was in a coma at the Queen
OL,11,FElizabeth Hospital in Birmingham for
OL,12,F27 days before having all the flesh on
OL,13,Fhis stomach, face and both arms
OL,14,Fremoved and replaced with the skin
OL,15,Ffrom his legs.
OL,17,FIn total he's had 23 operations and is
OL,18,Fcurrently waiting for a date for hand
OL,19,Fsurgery.
